result.execSummary:
The defendant Jena K. Klos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jena K. Klos is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jena K. Klos was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jena K. Klos in Court with Attorney Alex Stormont.  DA Sean Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called at 1:09 p.m.  Includes 15CF101 & 16CF19.  DA recites agreement; State moving to dismiss Count One of 15CF101, requesting one-year Probation on Count Two.  On Count One of 16CF19 State requesting two years Probation to run concurrent to 15CF101.  State moves to dismiss Counts Two, Three and Four.  Atty. Stormont agrees, Defendant agrees.  Atty. Stormont presents Plea Questionnaire, Court reviews and questions Defendant.  Court questions Defendant, advises of charges, possible penalties and rights.  Court advises re: felony, voter ineligibility and no possession of firearms.  Defendant understands and pleads Guilty to Count One of 16CF19 (Possesion of Meth) and Count Two (Poss. of Drug Paraphernalia) in 15CF101.  Atty. Stormont stipulated to facts.  Court accepts Pleas and adjudicates Defendant Guilty of Count One in 16CF19 and Count Two in 15CF101.  Court dismisses Count One of 15CF101 and Counts Two, Three and Four of 16CF19.  Attorneys make statements.  Defendant makes statement.  Court sentences Defendant; Sentence Withheld.  On Count One of 16CF19 orders two years Probation.  Defendant to comply with all conditions of Probation and pay court costs w/o DNA surcharge.  On Count Two of 15CF101 orders one year Probation, concurrent.  Defendant to pay court costs w/o DNA surcharge and follow all conditions of Probation.  Court advise of appeal rights.
Status conference on April 18, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Information Filed with the Court and a copy is given to the defendant.    Defendant has a copy of the information  and waives reading of the information.  Defendant enters not guilty plea to Counts 1, 2, 3 and 4 at preliminary hearing.  Not guilty plea received by the court on all 4 counts.    The bond will continue as ordered. Court reviews bond conditions with defendant.    Status Conference to  be set.  See JA for date.

10:36 a.m.  Defendant Jena K. Klos in court with attorney Alex Stormont.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Written waiver of preliminary hearing is filed and the court reviews with the defendant.    Court finds defendant freely, intelligently, knowingly, and understandingly made and waives constitutional right to a preliminary hearing.    The court finds probable cause and binds defendant over for further proceedings.
Defendant's Demand and Motion filed by Atty Stormont
Defendant waives her right to a preliminary hearing.
